18 among network participants linked together using cryptography to maintain the integrity of the ledger and to
19 execute other functions; and
20 (b) distributed among network participants in an automated fashion to concurrently update network
21 participants on the state of the ledger and any other functions.
22 (3) "Blockchain protocol" means any executable software deployed to a blockchain, typically
23 referred to as smart contracts, including an additional standardized set of rules that uses a previously existing
24 blockchain as a base, which facilitates the transfer of data and electronic records and allows that data to be
25 broadcast to nodes. The executable software is governed by a set of predefined rules that execute
26 autonomously without human intervention. The rules may be altered by a predetermined mechanism.
